062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15090,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/junub-before-fasting\/","url_meta":{"origin":15069,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Waking up in major impurity before fasting","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would wake up at dawn in a state of major impurity, then he would perform a ritual bath and observe fasting. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1925, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1109 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":992,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/08\/13\/sometimes-fasted-or-iftar\/","url_meta":{"origin":15069,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Companions fasted and broke fast during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 13, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas bin Malik reported: We would travel with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and those who fasted did not blame those who broke their fast, and those who broke their fast did not blame those who fasted. In another narration, Abu Sa'id al-Khudri said: Their view is\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-